Recap
Constructor
constructor is a special block of code that helps us initiliaze the instance fields/properties of a class
it is called automaticalle when we create and object of the class
While defining Constructor we do not mention that return type not even void
name of the constructor should be same as name of the class.
this.
when we have the same name-to show Java what exactly what we need to use.
this()
can be use with parenthesis to call the current class constructor.
we use this to avoid code repetition.
